[30;1m241 | [0m[35mWhen using the ``dns`` challenge, ``certbot`` will ask you to place a TXT DNS[0m
[30;1m242 | [0m[35mrecord with specific contents under the domain name consisting of the hostname[0m
[30;1m243 | [0m[35mfor which you want a certificate issued, prepended by ``_acme-challenge``.[0m
[30;1m244 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m245 | [0m[35mFor example, for the domain ``example.com``, a zone file entry would look like:[0m

[30;1m53 | [0m[35m our security model on Windows. With the default implementation[0m
[30;1m54 | [0m[35m# of os.chmod on Windows, almost all bits on mode will be ignored, and only a general RO or RW will[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m# be applied. The DACL, the inner mechanism to control file access on Windows, will stay on its[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35m# default definition, giving effectively at least read permissions to any one, as the default[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35m# permissions on root path will be inherit by the file (as NTFS state), and root path can be read[0m
[30;1m58 | [0m[35m# by anyone. So the given mode needs to be translated into a secured and not inherited DACL that[0m
